The equation is a linear state-space system with an impulse input. The solution is \( X(t) = e^{At} X_0 + \int_0^t e^{A(t-\tau)} b \, \delta(\tau) \, d\tau = e^{At} X_0 + e^{At} b \).  
Evaluating at \( t = 0^+ \) gives \( X(0^+) = X_0 + b = \begin{bmatrix} -1 \\ 0 \end{bmatrix} + \begin{bmatrix} 1 \\ 2 \end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix} 0 \\ 2 \end{bmatrix} \), so the second component is 2.  

\boxed{B}
